    <fr:title text="Forester 2.4 › wikilinks support"><fr:link href="foreign-forester-jms-007M.xml" title="Forester 2.4" addr="//forester/jms-007M" type="local">Forester 2.4</fr:link> › wikilinks support</fr:title>
    <fr:taxon>Feature</fr:taxon>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter>
    <fr:p>This release adds support for “wikilinks” in the form <fr:code><![CDATA[[[destination]]]]></fr:code>; this will be rendered as a link whose title is given by the title of the tree at address <fr:code>destination</fr:code>. Users are discouraged from using wikilinks heavily, as it is better for your mind to “work a link into a sentence” naturally; but this can be very useful for linking to <fr:link href="foreign-forester-jms-007K.xml" title="Creating your personal biographical tree" addr="//forester/jms-007K" type="local">biographical trees</fr:link> or daily notes.</fr:p>
  </fr:mainmatter>
